<p>When I add meta tag in if condition it destroy the UI <img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/sS6v7.png" alt="enter image description here"></p>  <p>     </p>  <pre><code>  &lt;!--[if IE lt 10]&gt;&lt;meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=7" /&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;  &lt;meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /&gt;    &lt;link id="lnkStyleSheet" href="" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" runat="server"/&gt; &lt;link href="~/Style/Controls.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" runat="server"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p></p>  <p>As you can see in the IE 7 browser it shows in the background.</p>